CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1960, pg. 3 reads: "Bak Atty. Washington - On the other side of the platform at the "Rebels" rally in behalf of the candidacy of Att. Linn Washington in 13th Ward to unseat Democratic Ward Chairman Sara Kirk were more of the candidates for committeman [sic] and committeewoman [sic] posts in the various districts. Left to right: Carrie Lewis, Alan Williams, Fleta McGuinn, Henry Ryan Mary Striblin, Daniel Gaitinelli, Mary Slaagle, Mattie Lackey, James Taylor, Mabel Gordon, James Johnson, Mary Turner and Donald Claytor."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Carrie Lewis, Alan Williams, Fleta McGuinn, Henry Ryan Mary Striblin, Daniel Gaitinelli, Mary Slaagle, Mattie Lackey, James Taylor, Mabel Gordon, James Johnson, Mary Turner, and Donald Claytor, seated in semicircle for rally by the 13th Ward "Rebels," Westinghouse High School auditorium
